<p>An oil and gas field worker earning $70,000 per year in Texas on a bi-weekly schedule ($2,692 gross per check) pays: $0 in Texas state income tax (no state income tax), $167 in Social Security (6.2%), $39 in Medicare (1.45%) -- net take-home approximately $2,208 per paycheck.</p>

